      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Subway Series</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Charles J Clark letter on New York Yankees-New York Mets day-night doubleheader on July 8; says if day-night plan is to truly to take on flavor of New York, why don't players take subway from Shea Stadium to Yankee Stadium?</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Day-Night Plan Is Set: It's Queens, Then Bronx'' (Sports pages, June 14): If the Yankees-Mets day-night doubleheader on July 8 is to truly take on the flavor of New York, why don't the players take the subway from Shea Stadium to Yankee Stadium?</p>
        <p>CHARLES J. CLARK  Somerset, N.J., June 14, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Day-Night Plan Is Set: It's Queens, Then Bronx'' (Sports pages, June 14): If the Yankees-Mets day-night doubleheader on July 8 is to truly take on the flavor of New York, why don't the players take the subway from Shea Stadium to Yankee Stadium?</p>
        <p>CHARLES J. CLARK  Somerset, N.J., June 14, 2000</p>
      </block>
